Bangladesh spin bowler Sohag Gazi
took a hat-trick of wickets as his team drew the first cricket
Test against New Zealand in Chittagong.  Gazi dismissed Corey Anderson, BJ Watling and Doug
Bracewell in consecutive balls in a haul of 6-77.  New Zealand had made 469 all out in its first innings,
including 114 by Kane Williamson and 103 by Watling. It declared
its second on 287-7.  Bangladesh finished on 173-3. It scored 501 all out in its
first innings, including 101 not out by Gazi and 181 by Mominul
Haque.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
